supplementary note 2 and supplementary data 1).;     after performing standard quality-control tests the resulting generic recon3d model contained 10600 reactions (78% of the reconstruction reactions) and was able to reproduce literature-consistent energy (atp) yields from different carbon sources (supplementary data 3â€“10) to fulfill metabolic functions describing cellular and whole body metabolism and to replicate the predictions of infant growth from a previous study25 (supplementary fig.;     enabling a 3d view of metabolism using a recently established approach26 the metabolic network content of recon3d was expanded to include 3d protein structures from the protein data bank (pdb)27 as well as homology models (fig. 2a supplementary fig. 5 and supplementary data 11â€“13).;     in addition we mapped content from a variety of external database resources to include metabolite structures (supplementary data 14).;     all mappings between snps pdb their representative domain hotspots and disease relevance are provided in supplementary data 15â€“20.;     all data mapping related to the somatic cancer mutations can be found in supplementary data 21â€“23).;     using a genetic algorithm the area under the curve (auc) of the receiver operating characteristic (roc) curve was maximized to predict the indication of the drug based on the type and degree of perturbation (fig. 6b supplementary data 24 and supplementary note 6).;     a total of 47 drug indications were analyzed in the context of the metabolic network based upon 1459 expression sets from cell culture responses to 334 drugs (supplementary data 26).;     our findings suggest that metabolic responses are significantly conserved for a wide range of drugs (fig. 6b) with the most conserved pathway perturbations nature biotechnology  volume 36  number 3  march 2018  occurring for antipsychotic drugs (median auc of 0.80; supplementary data 25).;     a list of the drugs with the most predictable metabolic responses is provided in supplementary data 26.;     first quek et al.55 reported 95 duplicate metabolites 71 of which were replaced (supplementary data 9 and supplementary note 1).;     third gene-protein-reaction associations were curated and corrected for 2180 reactions (supplementary data 6 and 7 and supplementary note 1).;     upon literature curation addition of the alternative route of methionine transamination and decarboxylation reactions were identified and added (supplementary data 1).;     please refer to supplementary note 1 and supplementary data 1â€“10 for detailed information on the network building and refinements.;     in the final master gem-pro data frame (supplementary data 11) we note where available homology models have been mapped to their respective genes.;     the chebi mapping procedure contained the following steps: (i) identification of the particular metabolite from chebi using the source link (the metabolite name was the starting point of search which is taken from the metabolite names in the supplementary data 14); (ii) checking the molecular formula and charge (neutral or charged) of the metabolite in the chebi database; (iii) capturing the chebi link chebi id smiles and inchi into the respective fields in the data set spreadsheet; (iv) 2d-structure is downloaded in .mol format.;     all selected missense variants and their drug associations have been provided as supplementary data 15 and 16.;     supplementary data 17 provides the mapping between the residue number of the uniprot missense variant > the pdb residue number > the pdb chain where the residue is located > the representative domain id linked to a given pdb chain > the structurally equivalent residue within that representative domain.;
